# HUD interaction tooltips

- **Every interactive control** in the extension new tab (`button`, icon-only actions, drag handles, and similar hit targets) **must** expose a **short plain-language description** of what happens when you use it. Prefer the shared wrapper **[`HudTip`](../../apps/extension/components/hud-tip.tsx)** so the hint uses the **digital HUD face** (**`font-display`** / Space Mono, uppercase, accent border + hard shadow) and appears on **hover** and **keyboard focus** (`group-focus-within`).
- **Do not rely on the native `title` attribute** for primary hints when `HudTip` is used (browser chrome uses a non-HUD font). You may keep `title` only where the control is **`disabled`** and some browsers skip custom hover layers.
- **Accessibility:** `HudTip` marks the bubble `aria-hidden`; the control itself still needs a correct **`aria-label`** (icon-only) and/or visible text. Do not put raw storage keys in tooltip copy; see [user-facing-copy.mdc](user-facing-copy.mdc).
- **Layout:** draggable HUD panels place a **drag handle** at the top-right (see [`tailwind.css`](../../apps/extension/entrypoints/newtab/tailwind.css) `.hud-drag-handle`). **Do not** place primary controls flush into that corner without **inline-end padding** (or another layout offset) so they stay clear of the handle.
